I think that the stereotypes of the Stepford wives have partly disappeared. The lives of women look, indeed, very different nowadays than in 1970s. It is commonly known that a wife is not obligated to cook, clean or submit at all to her husband. Women often have jobs now and their lives are not limited to being a maid. However, that is just a theory. In reality, statistics say that women still do much more housework than men. Wives cook, clean, take care of children or disabled family members and they do so while also being employed. It all results in, for example, lower salaries or pensions. The social status of women is fairly better than 50 years ago, but society has still a lot to do in terms of feminism.
